        "chunks": [
          {
            "cnum": 41,
            "text": "Investment Advisory Review: Feng Tay (9910) March revenue of NT$6.597 billion, a MOM of +13.5%, a YOY of -7.7%. Q1 2026 revenue of NT$19.235 billion, a YOY of -7.2%, a QOQ of -7.1%. Q1 2026 revenue achievement rate of 97.29%, slightly below expectations. In terms of profit, March preliminary operating income was NT$246 million, with an operating profit margin of 3.73%. Pre-tax net profit was NT$412 million, and net profit attributable to the parent company was NT$231 million, with an EPS of NT$0.23. Accumulated Q1 2026 operating income was NT$760 million, with an operating profit margin of 3.95% and an EPS of NT$0.68, below expectations. Looking ahead, Q2 is entering the peak season, and shipment volume is expected to increase. Major client NIKE stated in the previous earnings call that FY4Q26 (March 2026 - May 2026) revenue will decline by 2-4%, and revenue for the next nine months (March 2026 - November 2026) will decline by low single digits, implying that Feng Tay's shipment volume for NIKE may be difficult to grow this year. The overall outlook for 2026 is becoming more conservative, with H1 2026 expected to be flat, and the company aiming for flat shipment volume for the full year. 2025 EPS is NT$5.1, and 2026 EPS is revised down to NT$5.5. Short-term, due to the ongoing adjustment phase of its main client's operations, Feng Tay's business momentum is weakening. However, considering Feng Tay's long-term competitive advantages remain, we maintain a buy rating with a target price lowered to NT$100.",
